opennlp.ccg.lexicon
Class Lexicon

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.lexicon.Lexicon

public class Lexicon
extends Object

Contains words and their associated categories and semantics. Lookup can be filtered by plugging in a supertagger.

Version:
$Revision: 1.78 $, $Date: 2011/10/31 02:01:06 $
Author:

getSignsFromPred

public Collection<Sign> getSignsFromPred(String pred,
                                         List<String> coartRels)
Returns the lexical signs indexed by the given pred. If the pred is not listed in the lexicon, the tokenizer is consulted to see if it is a special token (date, time, etc.); otherwise, null is returned. Coarticulations are applied for the given rels, if non-null.

getEntriesFromWords

public List<SignHash> getEntriesFromWords(String s)
                                   throws LexException
For a string of 1 or more surface words, return all of the lexical entries for each word as a list of sign hashes. Tokenization is performed using the configured tokenizer.

Parameters:
w - the words in string format
Returns:
a list of sign hashes
Throws:
LexException - thrown if word not found

getSignsFromWord

public SignHash getSignsFromWord(Word w)
                          throws LexException
For a given word, return all of its surface word's lexical entries. If the word is not listed in the lexicon, the tokenizer is consulted to see if it is a special token (date, time, etc.); otherwise an exception is thrown. If the word has coarticulations, all applicable coarticulation entries are applied to the base word, in an arbitrary order.

Parameters:
w - the word
Returns:
a sign hash
Throws:
LexException - thrown if word not found
